		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_RESOURCE_CLAY_TEXT">
			<Text>Clay is a fine-grained soil that combines one or more clay minerals with traces of metal oxides and organic matter. Clays exhibit plasticity when mixed with water in certain proportions. When dry, clay becomes firm and when fired in a kiln, permanent physical and chemical changes occur. These reactions, among other changes, convert the clay into a ceramic material. Because of these properties, clay is used for making pottery, both utilitarian and decorative, and construction products, such as bricks, wall and floor tiles.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]--Wikipedia</Text>
